[2026-03-18T11:36:16.572Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Execute this requirement immediately without asking questions.\n\n## REQUIREMENT\n\n# Server-side encrypt credentials instead of trusting clients\n\n## Metadata\n- **Category**: code_quality\n- **Effort**: High (3/3)\n- **Impact**: Unknown (9/3)\n- **Scan Type**: zen_architect\n- **Generated**: 3/17/2026, 11:17:15 PM\n\n## Description\nThe POST /api/credentials endpoint accepts pre-encrypted data (encryptedData, iv, tag) directly from the client and stores it verbatim. This means the client must know the master key to encrypt, or the data is encrypted with a different key. Move encryption server-side: accept plaintext credential fields over TLS, encrypt with the servers master key in the handler, and store the result.\n\n## Reasoning\nThe current design either leaks the master key to clients or creates credentials encrypted with unknown keys that the server cannot decrypt. Server-side encryption is the only correct architecture for a multi-tenant credential store � the server is the trust boundary, not the client.\n\n\n## Recommended Skills\n\nUse Claude Code skills as appropriate for implementation guidance. Check `.claude/skills/` directory for available skills.\n\n## Notes\n\nThis requirement was generated from an AI-evaluated project idea. No specific goal is associated with this idea.\n\n## DURING IMPLEMENTATION\n\n- Use `get_memory` MCP tool when you encounter unfamiliar code or need context about patterns/files\n- Use `report_progress` MCP tool at each major phase (analyzing, planning, implementing, testing, validating)\n- Use `get_related_tasks` MCP tool before modifying shared files to check for parallel task conflicts\n\n## AFTER IMPLEMENTATION\n\n1. Log your implementation using the `log_implementation` MCP tool with:\n   - requirementName: the requirement filename (without .md)\n   - title: 2-6 word summary\n   - overview: 1-2 paragraphs describing what was done\n   - category: one of feature/bugfix/refactor/performance/security/infrastructure/ui/docs/test\n   - patternsApplied: comma-separated patterns used (e.g. \"repository pattern, debounce, memoization\")\n\n2. Verify: `npx tsc --noEmit` (fix any type errors)\n\nBegin implementation now."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"efe0d03e-8d66-4f31-bfdd-beb02c765aa8","uuid":"ec28b57d-1339-41f9-9cfb-59ab428a37c4","timestamp":"2026-03-18T11:36:16.489Z","isSynthetic":true}
