[2026-03-18T11:36:54.491Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GAanv3ZUwLhFKCbmwQr7dA","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have all the information needed. Let me provide a comprehensive summary of the credential storage and encryption flow.\n\n## Comprehensive Summary: Credential Storage and Encryption Flow\n\n### 1. **How Credentials Are Encrypted (Server-Side)**\n\nThe encryption happens **server-side** in the orchestrator:\n\n**Crypto Module** (`packages/shared/src/crypto.ts`):\n- Algorithm: **AES-256-GCM** (authenticated encryption)\n- Key derivation: **PBKDF2** with 100,000 iterations\n- IV length: 16 bytes (randomly generated per encryption)\n- Auth tag length: 16 bytes (for tamper detection)\n- Each credential stores: `encrypted` (hex), `iv` (hex), `tag` (hex)\n\n**Per-Tenant Key Derivation**:\n- Master secret + tenant-specific salt via `deriveTenantKey(masterSecret, tenantId)`\n- Tenant-specific salt format: `dac-tenant-v1:{tenantId}`\n- Ensures each tenant has a unique encryption key derived from the master secret\n\n---\n\n### 2. **POST /api/credentials Endpoint Handler**\n\n**Location**: `packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts` (lines 134-155)\n\n```\nRoute: POST /api/credentials\nHandler Logic:\n1. Parse request body (expects plaintext property)\n2. Validate plaintext size <= 64KB (MAX_PLAINTEXT_CHARS)\n3. If plaintext + tenantKeyManager available:\n   - Get tenant ID (body.projectId or ctx.projectId or 'default')\n   - Retrieve per-tenant key via tenantKeyManager.getKey(tenantId)\n   - Encrypt plaintext using encrypt(plaintext, key) from crypto module\n   - Store encrypted data, iv, and tag in body\n   - Delete plaintext from body before DB storage\n4. Call db.createCredential(tenantDb, body)\n5. Record audit event: action='key:encrypt', resourceType='credential'\n6. Return 201 with credential object\n```\n\n**Key Points**:\n- Oversized plaintexts are rejected before encryption (prevents blocking event loop)\n- Encryption happens server-side in the request handler\n- Audit log records the encryption action with tenant ID and credential ID\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Master Key Management**\n\n**Location**: `packages/orchestrator/src/config.ts`\n\n- **Master key source**: Environment variable `MASTER_KEY` (required)\n- **Type**: String\n- **Usage**: \n  - Passed to `TenantKeyManager` constructor\n  - Never stored in database\n  - Used only to derive per-tenant keys at runtime\n\n**Derivation Process**:\n- `deriveMasterKeyAsync(secret)` - async variant using pbkdf2 on libuv thread pool\n- `deriveTenantKey(masterSecret, tenantId)` - sync PBKDF2 with tenant-specific salt\n- `deriveTenantKeyAsync(masterSecret, tenantId)` - async variant\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Credential Decryption When Needed**\n\n**Location**: `packages/worker/src/credentialInjector.ts`\n\nThe worker does NOT decrypt credentials at rest. Instead:\n\n1. **File-Based Injection**: Credentials are written to temporary files (tmpfs/ramfs preferred)\n2. **Environment Variable Pointing**: Child process receives `DAC_CREDENTIALS_FILE` pointing to the file\n3. **File Cleanup**: Automatic cleanup after execution via `cleanup()` function\n4. **Security Features**:\n   - Files written to `/dev/shm` on Linux (tmpfs, never hits disk)\n   - Falls back to `os.tmpdir()` on other platforms\n   - File permissions: `0o600` (read/write by owner only)\n   - Exit handler synchronously removes files on process crash\n   - Orphaned files swept at startup (max age: 2 minutes)\n\n**Note**: The credentialInjector doesn't handle decryption - it assumes credentials are passed as plaintext env vars. The decryption happens in the orchestrator layer before sending to the worker.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Database Schema for Credentials**\n\n**Location**: `packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts` (lines 101-119)\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE persona_credentials (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',\n  name TEXT NOT NULL,\n  service_type TEXT NOT NULL,\n  encrypted_data TEXT NOT NULL,      -- AES-256-GCM ciphertext (hex)\n  iv TEXT NOT NULL,                   -- Initialization vector (hex)\n  tag TEXT NOT NULL,                  -- GCM authentication tag (hex)\n  metadata TEXT,                      -- Optional JSON metadata\n  last_used_at TEXT,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE persona_credential_links (\n  persona_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES personas(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n  credential_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES persona_credentials(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n  PRIMARY KEY (persona_id, credential_id)\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_pcred_project ON persona_credentials(project_id);\n```\n\n**CRUD Operations** (`packages/orchestrator/src/db/credentials.ts`):\n- `createCredential()` - Insert with all encryption fields\n- `getCredential()` - Full retrieval (includes encrypted data)\n- `listCredentialsForPersona()` - Join through links table\n- `linkCredential()` - Associate credential with persona\n- `deleteCredential()` - Remove with optional project scoping\n\n**Response Redaction** (httpApi.ts, line 163):\n- When listing credentials via `/api/personas/{id}/credentials`, encrypted fields are redacted: `[REDACTED]`\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Relevant Type Definitions**\n\n**Location**: `packages/shared/src/types.ts` (lines 92-104)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface PersonaCredential {\n  id: string;\n  projectId?: string;\n  name: string;\n  serviceType: string;\n  encryptedData: string;        // AES-256-GCM ciphertext (hex)\n  iv: string;                    // IV (hex)\n  tag: string;                   // Auth tag (hex)\n  metadata: string | null;       // Optional metadata\n  lastUsedAt: string | null;\n  createdAt: string;\n  updatedAt: string;\n}\n```\n\n**Crypto Interface** (`packages/shared/src/crypto.ts`, lines 13-17):\n\n```typescript\nexport interface EncryptedPayload {\n  encrypted: string;  // hex\n  iv: string;         // hex\n  tag: string;        // hex (GCM auth tag)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Tenant Key Manager**\n\n**Location**: `packages/orchestrator/src/tenantKeyManager.ts`\n\n**Purpose**: Manages per-tenant encryption keys with caching and automatic renewal\n\n**Key Features**:\n1. **Caching Strategy**:\n   - Default TTL: 30 minutes\n   - Renewal threshold: Renew 5 min before expiry\n   - Single maintenance timer every 60 seconds\n\n2. **Key Lifecycle**:\n   - `getKey(tenantId)` - Returns cached key or derives new one\n   - `warmTenant(tenantId)` - Eagerly pre-derive for a tenant\n   - `warmAll()` - Pre-warm all known tenants\n   - `invalidateAll()` - Clears all cached keys (e.g., after master key rotation)\n\n3. **Maintenance Phases**:\n   - Phase 1: Renew keys approaching expiry (proactive)\n   - Phase 2: Evict expired keys (cleanup)\n   - Fixed ordering prevents race conditions\n\n4. **Security**:\n   - Keys zeroed before removal: `key.fill(0)`\n   - Emits `key:derived` event for audit logging\n\n5. **Multi-Tenancy Support**:\n   - Derives unique key per tenant via PBKDF2\n   - Supports tenant source function for dynamic tenant discovery\n\n---\n\n### **Summary of Data Flow**\n\n```\nClient sends plaintext secret\n        ↓\nPOST /api/credentials handler\n        ↓\nValidate & size check\n        ↓\nGet per-tenant key from TenantKeyManager\n(derived from MASTER_KEY env var + tenantId)\n        ↓\nAES-256-GCM encrypt(plaintext, tenantKey)\nproduces: {encrypted, iv, tag}\n        ↓\nStore in persona_credentials table\n(encrypted_data, iv, tag columns)\n        ↓\nAudit log records encryption action\n        ↓\nReturn 201 with credential metadata\n```\n\nAll encryption is **server-side, per-tenant, authenticated**. The master key is environment-based, never persisted, and tenant keys are derived at runtime with 30-minute caching."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ae6b735ddaa31ba21 (use SendMessage with to: 'ae6b735ddaa31ba21' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 43047\ntool_uses: 10\nduration_ms: 26258</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"efe0d03e-8d66-4f31-bfdd-beb02c765aa8","uuid":"c0406af9-ec14-4be9-9c10-72af439faf46","timestamp":"2026-03-18T11:36:54.411Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the current credential storage and encryption flow in this project. \n\nFind and read:\n1. The POST /api/credentials endpoint handler (likely in packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts or similar)\n2. The crypto module (packages/shared/src/crypto.ts) \n3. Any credential-related types in packages/shared/src/types.ts\n4. The database layer that stores credentials (packages/orchestrator/src/db/ directory)\n5. packages/orchestrator/src/config.ts for master key configuration\n6. packages/worker/src/credentialInjector.ts for how credentials are decrypted/used\n7. packages/orchestrator/src/tenantKeyManager.ts for key management\n\nRead the full contents of all these files and provide a comprehensive summary of:\n- How credentials are currently encrypted (client-side vs server-side)\n- The exact HTTP handler for POST /api/credentials\n- How the master key is managed\n- How credentials are decrypted when needed\n- The database schema for credentials\n- Any relevant type definitions\n\nBe very thorough - read every file completely.","agentId":"ae6b735ddaa31ba21","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have all the information needed. Let me provide a comprehensive summary of the credential storage and encryption flow.\n\n## Comprehensive Summary: Credential Storage and Encryption Flow\n\n### 1. **How Credentials Are Encrypted (Server-Side)**\n\nThe encryption happens **server-side** in the orchestrator:\n\n**Crypto Module** (`packages/shared/src/crypto.ts`):\n- Algorithm: **AES-256-GCM** (authenticated encryption)\n- Key derivation: **PBKDF2** with 100,000 iterations\n- IV length: 16 bytes (randomly generated per encryption)\n- Auth tag length: 16 bytes (for tamper detection)\n- Each credential stores: `encrypted` (hex), `iv` (hex), `tag` (hex)\n\n**Per-Tenant Key Derivation**:\n- Master secret + tenant-specific salt via `deriveTenantKey(masterSecret, tenantId)`\n- Tenant-specific salt format: `dac-tenant-v1:{tenantId}`\n- Ensures each tenant has a unique encryption key derived from the master secret\n\n---\n\n### 2. **POST /api/credentials Endpoint Handler**\n\n**Location**: `packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts` (lines 134-155)\n\n```\nRoute: POST /api/credentials\nHandler Logic:\n1. Parse request body (expects plaintext property)\n2. Validate plaintext size <= 64KB (MAX_PLAINTEXT_CHARS)\n3. If plaintext + tenantKeyManager available:\n   - Get tenant ID (body.projectId or ctx.projectId or 'default')\n   - Retrieve per-tenant key via tenantKeyManager.getKey(tenantId)\n   - Encrypt plaintext using encrypt(plaintext, key) from crypto module\n   - Store encrypted data, iv, and tag in body\n   - Delete plaintext from body before DB storage\n4. Call db.createCredential(tenantDb, body)\n5. Record audit event: action='key:encrypt', resourceType='credential'\n6. Return 201 with credential object\n```\n\n**Key Points**:\n- Oversized plaintexts are rejected before encryption (prevents blocking event loop)\n- Encryption happens server-side in the request handler\n- Audit log records the encryption action with tenant ID and credential ID\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Master Key Management**\n\n**Location**: `packages/orchestrator/src/config.ts`\n\n- **Master key source**: Environment variable `MASTER_KEY` (required)\n- **Type**: String\n- **Usage**: \n  - Passed to `TenantKeyManager` constructor\n  - Never stored in database\n  - Used only to derive per-tenant keys at runtime\n\n**Derivation Process**:\n- `deriveMasterKeyAsync(secret)` - async variant using pbkdf2 on libuv thread pool\n- `deriveTenantKey(masterSecret, tenantId)` - sync PBKDF2 with tenant-specific salt\n- `deriveTenantKeyAsync(masterSecret, tenantId)` - async variant\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Credential Decryption When Needed**\n\n**Location**: `packages/worker/src/credentialInjector.ts`\n\nThe worker does NOT decrypt credentials at rest. Instead:\n\n1. **File-Based Injection**: Credentials are written to temporary files (tmpfs/ramfs preferred)\n2. **Environment Variable Pointing**: Child process receives `DAC_CREDENTIALS_FILE` pointing to the file\n3. **File Cleanup**: Automatic cleanup after execution via `cleanup()` function\n4. **Security Features**:\n   - Files written to `/dev/shm` on Linux (tmpfs, never hits disk)\n   - Falls back to `os.tmpdir()` on other platforms\n   - File permissions: `0o600` (read/write by owner only)\n   - Exit handler synchronously removes files on process crash\n   - Orphaned files swept at startup (max age: 2 minutes)\n\n**Note**: The credentialInjector doesn't handle decryption - it assumes credentials are passed as plaintext env vars. The decryption happens in the orchestrator layer before sending to the worker.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Database Schema for Credentials**\n\n**Location**: `packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts` (lines 101-119)\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE persona_credentials (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',\n  name TEXT NOT NULL,\n  service_type TEXT NOT NULL,\n  encrypted_data TEXT NOT NULL,      -- AES-256-GCM ciphertext (hex)\n  iv TEXT NOT NULL,                   -- Initialization vector (hex)\n  tag TEXT NOT NULL,                  -- GCM authentication tag (hex)\n  metadata TEXT,                      -- Optional JSON metadata\n  last_used_at TEXT,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE persona_credential_links (\n  persona_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES personas(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n  credential_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES persona_credentials(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n  PRIMARY KEY (persona_id, credential_id)\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_pcred_project ON persona_credentials(project_id);\n```\n\n**CRUD Operations** (`packages/orchestrator/src/db/credentials.ts`):\n- `createCredential()` - Insert with all encryption fields\n- `getCredential()` - Full retrieval (includes encrypted data)\n- `listCredentialsForPersona()` - Join through links table\n- `linkCredential()` - Associate credential with persona\n- `deleteCredential()` - Remove with optional project scoping\n\n**Response Redaction** (httpApi.ts, line 163):\n- When listing credentials via `/api/personas/{id}/credentials`, encrypted fields are redacted: `[REDACTED]`\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Relevant Type Definitions**\n\n**Location**: `packages/shared/src/types.ts` (lines 92-104)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface PersonaCredential {\n  id: string;\n  projectId?: string;\n  name: string;\n  serviceType: string;\n  encryptedData: string;        // AES-256-GCM ciphertext (hex)\n  iv: string;                    // IV (hex)\n  tag: string;                   // Auth tag (hex)\n  metadata: string | null;       // Optional metadata\n  lastUsedAt: string | null;\n  createdAt: string;\n  updatedAt: string;\n}\n```\n\n**Crypto Interface** (`packages/shared/src/crypto.ts`, lines 13-17):\n\n```typescript\nexport interface EncryptedPayload {\n  encrypted: string;  // hex\n  iv: string;         // hex\n  tag: string;        // hex (GCM auth tag)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Tenant Key Manager**\n\n**Location**: `packages/orchestrator/src/tenantKeyManager.ts`\n\n**Purpose**: Manages per-tenant encryption keys with caching and automatic renewal\n\n**Key Features**:\n1. **Caching Strategy**:\n   - Default TTL: 30 minutes\n   - Renewal threshold: Renew 5 min before expiry\n   - Single maintenance timer every 60 seconds\n\n2. **Key Lifecycle**:\n   - `getKey(tenantId)` - Returns cached key or derives new one\n   - `warmTenant(tenantId)` - Eagerly pre-derive for a tenant\n   - `warmAll()` - Pre-warm all known tenants\n   - `invalidateAll()` - Clears all cached keys (e.g., after master key rotation)\n\n3. **Maintenance Phases**:\n   - Phase 1: Renew keys approaching expiry (proactive)\n   - Phase 2: Evict expired keys (cleanup)\n   - Fixed ordering prevents race conditions\n\n4. **Security**:\n   - Keys zeroed before removal: `key.fill(0)`\n   - Emits `key:derived` event for audit logging\n\n5. **Multi-Tenancy Support**:\n   - Derives unique key per tenant via PBKDF2\n   - Supports tenant source function for dynamic tenant discovery\n\n---\n\n### **Summary of Data Flow**\n\n```\nClient sends plaintext secret\n        ↓\nPOST /api/credentials handler\n        ↓\nValidate & size check\n        ↓\nGet per-tenant key from TenantKeyManager\n(derived from MASTER_KEY env var + tenantId)\n        ↓\nAES-256-GCM encrypt(plaintext, tenantKey)\nproduces: {encrypted, iv, tag}\n        ↓\nStore in persona_credentials table\n(encrypted_data, iv, tag columns)\n        ↓\nAudit log records encryption action\n        ↓\nReturn 201 with credential metadata\n```\n\nAll encryption is **server-side, per-tenant, authenticated**. The master key is environment-based, never persisted, and tenant keys are derived at runtime with 30-minute caching."}],"totalDurationMs":26258,"totalTokens":43047,"totalToolUseCount":10,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10705,"cache_read_input_tokens":30187,"output_tokens":2150,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":10705},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
